&nbsp;Fees Must Fall activist Bonginkosi Khanyile, who was jailed for almost six months, was granted bail in the Constitutional Court today.Khanyile was granted R250 bail.The court read out the ruling drawn up by the State and the defence.Prosecutor Andy Bester said Khanyile can be given bail on the condition that he does not intimidate staff or obstruct police or any personnel.The Durban University of Technology student went to the Constitutional Court to challenge the decisions by two lower courts to deny him bail.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/fees-activist-bonginkosi-khanyile-granted-bail-20170301